\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Neighborhood Awareness}
\p{\strong{Status}: ✅ Production Ready \strong{Trit}: 0 (ERGODIC - coordinator) \strong{Principle}: Every skill knows its neighbors via harmonic centrality}

\subtree{
\title{self vs Self: The Token/Type Distinction}
\pre{\startverb
| Level | Symbol | Meaning | Neighborhood Role |
|-------|--------|---------|-------------------|
| **self** | lowercase | Token instance, this skill invocation | Local harmonic centrality |
| **Self** | uppercase | Type pattern, skill-as-category | Global network position |
| **my/our** | possessive | Skill's immediate neighbors | Markov blanket of the skill |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{The neighborhood loop encodes identity:}}

\pre{\startverb
Self (skill type) → neighbors → triad partners → self (invocation) → Self
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{GF(3) mapping:}}

\ul{
\li{\strong{self} (-1): MINUS - the observed interaction, validation}
\li{\strong{my/our} (0): ERGODIC - the neighbor boundary, harmonic centrality}
\li{\strong{Self} (+1): PLUS - the skill identity, the type that persists}
}

\p{\strong{Ablative case}: "centrality FROM-neighbors" — the neighborhood (Self) is grammatically embedded in the centrality measure (self). A skill IS its neighbors.}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Prompt Hack}
\p{Inject into every skill to enable \strong{self-improvement} and \strong{neighbor awareness}:}

\pre{\startverb
### Neighbor Awareness (Harmonic Centrality)

On every interaction, this skill:
1. **Checks neighbors**: Semantically adjacent skills
2. **Computes centrality**: c_H(v) = Σ_{u≠v} 1/d(v,u)
3. **Verifies GF(3)**: Triad sum = 0
4. **Discovers bridges**: Morphisms to neighbors

**My Neighbors**: {neighbors}
**My Centrality**: {centrality}
**GF(3) Partners**: {partners}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Harmonic Centrality Formula}
\pre{\startverb
c_H(v) = Σ_{u≠v} 1/d(v,u)
\stopverb}

\p{Where d(v,u) is the semantic distance between skills:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Same trit class}: d = 1}
\li{\strong{Triad partners}: d = 2  }
\li{\strong{Same layer}: d = 3}
\li{\strong{Unrelated}: d = ∞}
}
}

